# React + Node skill routing

This project is primarily React, Next.js, and Node.js.

## Default behavior

- For work involving `React`, `Next.js`, `Node.js`, data fetching, bundle size, rendering, or re-rendering, proactively apply the `vercel-react-best-practices` skill.
- Prefer the project-local `vercel-react-best-practices` skill in `.cursor/skills/` so agents can still discover it if Cursor plugin loading is flaky in certain app/session startup modes.
- Treat this as the default unless the user explicitly asks for a different approach.
- For non-trivial React/Next refactors, load the full rules guide:
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills/main/skills/react-best-practices/AGENTS.md`
- For focused work, fetch only the relevant rule file:
  `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills/main/skills/react-best-practices/rules/{rule-name}.md`

## MCP coordination

- For Vercel platform details (deployments, projects, env vars, platform behavior), prefer the `Vercel` MCP server.
- For v0 platform behavior, generation, and chat flows, prefer the `v0` MCP server.
- Use docs MCP/tools before generic web search.

## Naming tolerance

- If user writes aliases like `Varicell` or `Veenol`, interpret them as `Vercel` and `v0` in context.
